issue.title: Stop proceeding with constant folding if a CPU kernel is not found found

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
Constant folding assumes that every node in the graph will have a CPU kernel which is strictly not true as we only support a subset of types in some CPU kernels. In those cases, we cannot constant fold and stop.

Fix #3735
